text: Jan Friš (born 19 December 1995) is a Czech middle-distance runner specialising in the 1500 metres. He won the silver medal at the 2019 Summer Universiade. ==International competitions== {| |- !colspan="6"|Representing the |- |2014 |World Junior Championships |Eugene, United States |24th (h) |3000 m s'chase |9:20.52 |- |2015 |European Indoor Championships |Prague, Czech Republic |12th (h) |1500 m |3:47.16 |- |rowspan=2|2017 |European Indoor Championships |Belgrade, Serbia |16th (h) |1500 m |3:50.38 |- |European U23 Championships |Bydgoszcz, Poland |22nd (h) |1500 m |3:47.73 |- |rowspan=3|2019 |European Indoor Championships |Birmingham, United Kingdom |19th (h) |1500 m |3:49.59 |- |rowspan=2|Universiade |rowspan=2|Naples, Italy |bgcolor=silver|2nd |1500 m |3:53.95 |- |8th (h) |4 × 400 m relay |3:10.77 |} ==Personal bests== Outdoor *800 metres – 1:49.47 (Turnov 2018) *1000 metres – 2:20.05 (Ostrava 2017) *1500 metres – 3:40.85 (Dessau 2019) *One mile – 4:01.41 (Ostrava 2019) *3000 metres – 8:03.54 (Pliezhausen 2019) *5000 metres – 14:34.49 (Tampere 2019) *3000 metres steeplechase – 9:01.13 (Plzeň 2019) Indoor *800 metres – 1:50.51 (Ostrava 2017) *1500 metres – 3:41.96 (Kirchberg 2019) *One mile – 4:08.96 (Athlone 2018) *3000 metres – 8:10.70 (Ostrava 2018) ==References== Category:1995 births Category:Living people Category:Czech male middle-distance runners Category:Sportspeople from Prague Category:Czech Athletics Championships winners Category:Universiade silver medalists for the Czech Republic Category:Universiade medalists in athletics (track and field) Category:Medalists at the 2019 Summer Universiade
